news.title: L&T sells three pre-leased floors in Powai office tower to National Realty for Rs 81 crore
news.para: The company sold this office with nearly 37,527 sq ft carpet area immediately after leasing it to CitiusTech Healthcare Technology at starting annual rent of Rs 7.40 crore.

news.title: Why 2.5 lakh flats' registries are stuck in Noida
news.para: For long, homebuyers had pinned hopes on the apex court judgment related to the rate of land dues, anticipating that builders will clear their dues as per the court order and the registry of flats will finally start.

news.title: Many haven't shifted to new flats yet, but Noida authority starts demolition of slums
news.para: The move comes nearly three years after the Authority allotted 2,064 newly-built flats in Sector 122 to slum residents under the jhuggi jhopri rehabilitation scheme.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA commences e-registration of flats from its premises
news.para: Aiming to boost e-registration of flats from developer’s office training was given to builders and software was shared so that developers could carry out registration of new flats from its own offices.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body likely to fall short of Rs 2,000 crore property tax target
news.para: So far, the GHMC has earned 1,522 crore in revenue through property tax. While bill collectors have been pressed into action to collect arrears from property owners, officials remain sceptical of achieving the remaining 478 crore target in 20 days.

news.title: Sikar police to visit Gujarat to seize properties in real estate scam
news.para: The investigation so far has suggested that the accused bought nearly 1,000 beeghas of land in Dholera and other properties in Gujarat from the money of investors.

news.title: DRT orders Bank of Baroda to refund forfeited amount
news.para: In this case, one Mohammedarif Qureshi was a successful bidder for Rs 3.21 crore for purchase of a property in Anand when the bank held an auction.

news.title: Government to construct 25,000 EWS houses in phased manner: Punjab housing minister
news.para: ​Replying to a question in the state assembly here, the minister said nearly 15,000 dwelling units will be constructed in the first phase under the Punjab EWS Housing Policy.

news.title: Bank of Maharashtra cuts home loan rate to 8.4%
news.para: Besides, it said, the bank has also a special rate of interest (ROI) for defence personnel, including paramilitary forces, benefiting salaried and pensioner categories for home loans.

news.title: China: CIFI Holdings expects to swing to a loss for 2022
news.para: The Shanghai-based company expects to post a core net loss of between 5.10 billion yuan ($734 million) and 5.60 billion yuan for the year ended Dec. 31, 2022, compared to a profit of 7.28 billion yuan recorded a year earlier.

news.title: Accused knew of all circumstances that led to Chintels Paradiso collapse, says CBI chargesheet
news.para: They allegedly not only overlooked the circumstances but Austin, in a bid to escape from the liability, also managed to get two backdated agreements of repair from an Amroha-based labour contractor, reveals the chargesheet filed by CBI’s special crime branch (SCB) in the court of CBI special magistrate Vinod Kumar last week.

news.title: Gujarat government collected Rs 1,606 crore from construction cess in three years
news.para: The government said that in the financial year 2020-21, the cess collection was Rs 452.92 crore. This rose to Rs 572.24 crore in 2021-22, an increase of 26.34%.

news.title: Patna civic body organises camps for holding tax collection
news.para: The PMC deployed teams in Sector-A of all the wards on Friday for the convenience of the residents. Each sector will host the camp for two days.

news.title: Lucknow civic body to collect property tax on weekends
news.para: Chief taxation officer, LMC, Ashok Singh said, “The civic body has collected Rs 273.15 crore as property tax till March 10 in this financial year. The civic body had collected around Rs 250 crore during the same period in the last financial year. "

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 14,000 properties over tax default
news.para: The tax and revenue department sealed 4,565 properties in the east zone, 2,605 properties in the west zone, 2,110 properties in the south zone and 1,600 properties in the south west zone.
